WEBVTT

00:01.235 --> 00:03.302
Oh, what a difference
a week makes.

00:03.304 --> 00:04.436
After trailing his opponents
in the first round

00:04.438 --> 00:05.938
of Republican primaries,

00:05.940 --> 00:07.639
Hollis Doyle
has now taken the lead.

00:07.641 --> 00:09.942
I'm giving America
back to Americans.

00:09.944 --> 00:11.643
No more of these
south-of-the-border types

00:11.645 --> 00:12.978
with their greedy little hands,

00:12.980 --> 00:14.380
or these shady fellas
with mustaches

00:14.382 --> 00:15.981
looking to blow up
our buildings.

00:15.983 --> 00:18.951
This is our country.
I aim to keep it that way.

00:18.953 --> 00:21.854
Look at them. It's like
Throwback Thursday in there.

00:21.856 --> 00:23.188
A Gladiator reunion.

00:23.190 --> 00:24.656
-This is good?
-This is so good.

00:24.658 --> 00:26.492
-This is not good.
-This is good. Let it be good.

00:26.494 --> 00:27.292
Can't let it be good
if it's not good.

00:27.294 --> 00:28.827
And that is not good.

00:28.829 --> 00:31.030
That looks good,
but that is<i> not</i> good.

00:31.032 --> 00:32.698
Trust me.

00:32.700 --> 00:34.199
So, we are agreed, then.
Until Hollis Doyle goes down...

00:34.201 --> 00:36.135
No more campaigning
against each other.

00:36.137 --> 00:38.037
-Mellie backs off of Susan.
-Susan backs off of Mellie.

00:38.039 --> 00:39.271
-We can do this.
-We can do this.

00:48.649 --> 00:50.749
[ Sighs ]

00:53.087 --> 00:55.354
Start gathering intel. I need
something lethal on Susan.

00:55.356 --> 00:56.655
What about the cease-fire?

00:56.657 --> 00:57.990
Cease-fires get broken.

00:57.992 --> 00:59.958
I want to make sure
we're protected.

01:02.763 --> 01:03.862
Don't even.

01:03.864 --> 01:05.330
It can still be good.
There's time.

01:05.332 --> 01:07.066
They are never gonna be
what they were, Quinn.

01:07.068 --> 01:10.736
Deep down, Abby is one of us.
It can still be good.

01:12.873 --> 01:15.407
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

01:16.544 --> 01:17.543
-You rang?
-Yeah.

01:17.545 --> 01:19.545
We're gonna need
some dirt.

01:19.547 --> 01:21.046
-On Hollis?
-On Mellie.

01:21.048 --> 01:23.949
If these talks break down,
and I think they might,

01:23.951 --> 01:26.285
we're gonna have a war
on our hands.

01:26.287 --> 01:28.787
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

01:34.228 --> 01:35.961
[ Door opens ]

01:38.365 --> 01:39.431
I came to take you to lunch.

01:39.433 --> 01:41.033
I don't have time
to go to lunch.

01:41.035 --> 01:43.202
I have to sit here and come up
with neutral things to say

01:43.204 --> 01:44.970
about Mellie Grant
for my press conference,

01:44.972 --> 01:45.938
so I can't go to lunch.

01:45.940 --> 01:49.141
Which is why
I brought lunch to you.

01:49.143 --> 01:50.809
Gettysburger!

01:50.811 --> 01:53.045
You are
a truly special human being.

01:53.047 --> 01:55.147
Why are you saying
neutral things about Mellie?

01:55.149 --> 01:56.782
Ugh.

01:56.784 --> 01:58.417
Because we're in a cease-fire
with the Grant campaign,

01:58.419 --> 01:59.818
which is killing me.

01:59.820 --> 02:01.487
Mellie wants to end
Medicare.

02:01.489 --> 02:02.788
The woman hates old people.

02:02.790 --> 02:04.957
But I have to smile
and be neutral

02:04.959 --> 02:06.959
because we are going to
burn Hollis Doyle

02:06.961 --> 02:09.061
and his hillbilly hate
to the ground.

02:09.063 --> 02:11.330
Hmm.
Eyes on the prize.

02:11.332 --> 02:12.798
It works.

02:12.800 --> 02:15.667
I'm about to argue a case
before the Supreme Court

02:15.669 --> 02:17.603
about whether
the federal government is liable

02:17.605 --> 02:19.104
for a regulatory taking

02:19.106 --> 02:21.273
based on the United States
Corps of Engineers' denial

02:21.275 --> 02:22.808
of a permit under Section 404

02:22.810 --> 02:25.277
of the Clean Water Act
to fill wetlands.

02:25.279 --> 02:26.678
That's interesting.

02:26.680 --> 02:28.981
No.
It's lethally dull.

02:28.983 --> 02:31.116
But eyes on the prize.

02:31.118 --> 02:33.952
Every time I hear the word
"wetlands" and "clean water,"

02:33.954 --> 02:35.587
I focus
on some beach vacation

02:35.589 --> 02:37.422
the two of us might take
someday.

02:37.424 --> 02:39.791
Hopefully soon.

02:39.793 --> 02:41.760
You want to take me
on a vacation?

02:41.762 --> 02:43.595
I'm saying
it's a trick I use.

02:43.597 --> 02:45.797
If I have
a dull antitrust case,

02:45.799 --> 02:48.267
I remember that antitrust
pretty much defines

02:48.269 --> 02:50.202
how you thought about me
for a long time,

02:50.204 --> 02:51.870
and rightfully so.

02:51.872 --> 02:54.973
And I'll focus on all the ways
I intend to make it up to you.

02:54.975 --> 02:58.644
A Fair Housing Act case
will get me thinking

02:58.646 --> 03:00.045
of the house
we might live in together.

03:00.047 --> 03:02.814
And ERISA cases,
normally the worst --

03:02.816 --> 03:06.018
The Employee Retirement
Income Security Act --

03:06.020 --> 03:08.053
Well, I don't care
about those anymore, either.

03:08.055 --> 03:09.821
Because they help me imagine
the two of us

03:09.823 --> 03:10.856
getting old together,

03:10.858 --> 03:13.992
and I'd like for us
to get old together.

03:13.994 --> 03:15.093
Eyes on the prize.

03:17.164 --> 03:18.697
Mm-hmm.

03:22.136 --> 03:24.069
What is happening?

03:24.071 --> 03:26.371
David.

03:28.142 --> 03:29.575
David?

03:29.577 --> 03:30.342
I would think
that it's clear.

03:30.344 --> 03:31.877
No. No!

03:31.879 --> 03:33.879
It's not clear.
It's not clear to me.

03:33.881 --> 03:36.748
I mean, I think it is,
but I don't want to be a woman

03:36.750 --> 03:39.418
who thinks a thing is happening
that's not happening.

03:39.420 --> 03:40.786
-It's happening.
-No!

03:42.089 --> 03:44.256
I'm gonna need you
to say it.

03:44.258 --> 03:46.592
Just say it clearly
in a full sentence.

03:46.594 --> 03:47.993
All the words.

03:47.995 --> 03:49.661
[ Clears throat ]

03:49.663 --> 03:51.029
Fine.

03:51.031 --> 03:52.731
I may or may not be asking --
suggesting --

03:52.733 --> 03:54.233
that we get married.

03:54.235 --> 03:56.101
If you want to.
This is your decision.

03:56.103 --> 03:57.869
It's the 21st century.

03:57.871 --> 03:59.938
We could mutually decide
to join our lives together

03:59.940 --> 04:01.206
if you should so choose --

04:01.208 --> 04:03.108
Shhh!

04:07.848 --> 04:09.982
Ask me
like a normal person.

04:15.022 --> 04:18.957
Susan...

04:18.959 --> 04:20.626
will you marry me?

04:26.767 --> 04:29.167
[ Laughs lightly ]

04:32.640 --> 04:34.039
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

04:34.041 --> 04:35.307
Cyrus.

04:35.309 --> 04:37.309
Olivia.

04:37.311 --> 04:38.343
Thanks for coming.

04:41.448 --> 04:44.216
You think I'm out of touch?
You think I've lost it?

04:44.218 --> 04:45.784
That's why you called me?
Cyrus --

04:45.786 --> 04:47.319
Liv.

04:47.321 --> 04:48.086
I'm s-- please.

04:48.088 --> 04:50.155
[ Sighs ]

04:50.157 --> 04:51.657
[ Sighs ]

04:52.593 --> 04:54.393
Talk.
Frankie is brilliant.

04:54.395 --> 04:56.728
Smart, quick.
But also warm, personable.

04:56.730 --> 04:58.897
When people hand him
their babies to hold,

04:58.899 --> 05:00.766
his face
actually lights up.

05:00.768 --> 05:04.136
Not that politician grin
everyone gets.

05:04.138 --> 05:05.837
His face fills
with human joy

05:05.839 --> 05:07.939
because he likes
holding people's babies.

05:07.941 --> 05:11.109
He likes talking to people.
He doesn't mind touching people.

05:11.111 --> 05:13.912
He'll hug old ladies
and pray with those sickos

05:13.914 --> 05:16.315
you always got to visit
in hospitals on the trail.

05:16.317 --> 05:17.849
And, Liv?

05:17.851 --> 05:20.218
He truly wants to
make the country a better place.

05:21.989 --> 05:25.157
He wants to help people.

05:27.261 --> 05:28.760
He's pure.

05:28.762 --> 05:31.797
They love him like he's Kennedy
and King rolled into one.

05:31.799 --> 05:35.834
He is a rockstar
on the campaign trail,

05:35.836 --> 05:38.704
but he's still losing
every other primary.

05:40.441 --> 05:42.441
You believe
he's the real thing.

05:45.346 --> 05:46.511
Yes.

05:46.513 --> 05:47.946
No.

05:47.948 --> 05:50.349
You believe.

05:50.351 --> 05:52.284
You.
Cyrus Beene.

05:52.286 --> 05:53.452
You're a believer.

05:53.454 --> 05:55.687
Cyrus, that's --

05:55.689 --> 05:58.390
He's losing
to Edison Davis.

05:58.392 --> 05:59.925
And there's no reason
why he should be.

06:02.162 --> 06:05.063
I keep looking for something,
but maybe it's me.

06:05.065 --> 06:06.665
Maybe I'm done.

06:06.667 --> 06:09.468
Maybe you only get one or two
presidential elections.

06:09.470 --> 06:13.071
If I've lost my touch

06:13.073 --> 06:14.806
[sighs]
if I'm bad at this now,

06:14.808 --> 06:17.476
too old for the gig,
I need to know.

06:17.478 --> 06:19.845
You need to tell me
so I can get out right now,

06:19.847 --> 06:21.480
before I do him
any more damage.

06:28.055 --> 06:29.688
It's not you.

06:29.690 --> 06:33.191
You're not losing
to Edison.

06:33.193 --> 06:35.160
You're losing
to my father.

06:36.997 --> 06:38.430
He's running
Edison's campaign?

06:38.432 --> 06:40.232
He's running Edison.

06:40.234 --> 06:42.534
He's running everything
and everyone.

06:42.536 --> 06:44.603
So, what are we doing?

06:44.605 --> 06:46.271
[ Sighs ]

06:46.273 --> 06:47.906
What's the plan?

06:47.908 --> 06:50.742
Because I'm happy
to go all-in

06:50.744 --> 06:52.677
with whatever
you've got going on.

06:52.679 --> 06:54.679
And I'll do
some dirty work.

06:54.681 --> 06:57.015
I mean, I know you say
you won't kill him

06:57.017 --> 06:58.950
because he's your dad,
but let's at least talk about --

06:58.952 --> 07:00.685
Cyrus!

07:00.687 --> 07:02.854
I am not fighting my father,
because there's no way to win.

07:02.856 --> 07:04.689
And even if there was,
I'm done trying.

07:04.691 --> 07:06.024
What about Mellie?

07:06.026 --> 07:08.293
You think this won't be an issue
in the general election?

07:08.295 --> 07:09.895
You think he won't steal
the presidency

07:09.897 --> 07:11.296
right out from under
the American people's

07:11.298 --> 07:12.798
piggy little noses?

07:12.800 --> 07:16.034
My father was Command,
Cyrus.

07:16.036 --> 07:18.203
We both know
he'll do a better job

07:18.205 --> 07:20.205
of stealing the Oval
than we ever did.

07:21.575 --> 07:22.541
Olivia --

07:22.543 --> 07:24.643
Good luck, Cyrus.

07:28.715 --> 07:30.749
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

07:30.751 --> 07:33.718
♪♪

07:38.992 --> 07:40.091
Rowan: Hello, Abigail.

07:40.093 --> 07:41.927
Is Olivia in trouble?
What do you want?

07:41.929 --> 07:43.094
This is not about Olivia.

07:43.096 --> 07:44.429
Well, in that case...

07:44.431 --> 07:46.331
It's about you.
What you want.

07:46.333 --> 07:47.566
And what do I want?

07:47.568 --> 07:49.067
Susan Ross in the Oval.

07:49.069 --> 07:52.103
This will crush Mellie
and give your gal a real shot.

07:52.105 --> 07:54.005
How did you know I was
looking for dirt on Mellie?

07:54.007 --> 07:55.407
[ Chuckles ]
Well, you really don't know me.

07:55.409 --> 07:57.175
First of all,
I'm a little more focused

07:57.177 --> 07:58.910
on Hollis right now
than I am Mellie.

07:58.912 --> 08:00.111
And once Hollis is
dispatched,

08:00.113 --> 08:01.847
you're simply gonna lie in bed
peacefully

08:01.849 --> 08:03.281
and wait for Olivia
to smother you with a pillow?

08:03.283 --> 08:04.649
Goodbye.

08:04.651 --> 08:07.319
Olivia aborted President
Fitzgerald Grant's baby.

08:07.321 --> 08:10.422
♪♪

08:15.629 --> 08:17.963
Ask yourself
a simple question.

08:17.965 --> 08:20.665
What would Olivia Pope do?

08:30.777 --> 08:31.810
Our target for destruction?
Hollis Doyle.

08:31.812 --> 08:33.011
The devil you love
to have a beer with.

08:33.013 --> 08:34.546
-This should be easy.
-Don't be too sure.

08:34.548 --> 08:35.847
No matter what he does,
America loves him.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.182
His supporters
certainly do.

08:37.184 --> 08:38.450
These should help
with that.

08:38.452 --> 08:39.851
-What's that?
-Oppo.
-Oppo.

08:39.853 --> 08:41.319
Olivia:
It's oppo research.

08:41.321 --> 08:42.621
Enough to attack him
from three angles.

08:42.623 --> 08:44.222
To drive wedges
between his support

08:44.224 --> 08:45.624
from three important groups.

08:45.626 --> 08:47.125
Fiscal conservatives,
women,

08:47.127 --> 08:49.060
and anyone with
the slightest sense of decency.

08:49.062 --> 08:50.562
What do you got?

08:50.564 --> 08:53.131
Hollis Doyle stole tax money
from hardworking Americans.

08:53.133 --> 08:55.066
Have you see the reports
that Hollis Doyle

08:55.068 --> 08:57.168
took billions
of taxpayer bailout money,

08:57.170 --> 08:59.137
then used it to buy an island
in the Caribbean?

08:59.139 --> 09:01.540
While I can't comment
on an ongoing investigation,

09:01.542 --> 09:03.308
if true,
this is beyond shameful,

09:03.310 --> 09:06.177
and the very antithesis
of what this country is about.

09:06.179 --> 09:09.648
Look, ol' Fitzy's part of what
I call the lucky sperm club.

09:09.650 --> 09:11.850
Never worked
a day in his life.

09:11.852 --> 09:14.419
Looks down on us
hardworking new-money folks.

09:14.421 --> 09:16.922
Still. He's welcome
on my island anytime

09:16.924 --> 09:19.057
so long as he keeps
his drawers on.

09:19.059 --> 09:21.326
I don't want him waving
his tiny flag around,

09:21.328 --> 09:22.827
scaring all the natives.

09:22.829 --> 09:25.163
[ Laughs ]
You feel me?

09:25.165 --> 09:26.431
Hollis Doyle is a rapist.

09:26.433 --> 09:27.599
-Rapist?
-Who?

09:27.601 --> 09:29.534
-His wife.
-His second wife.

09:29.536 --> 09:33.004
He grabbed my hair
and pulled me to the floor.

09:33.006 --> 09:35.941
I screamed. Fought.
Begged for him to stop.

09:35.943 --> 09:37.943
So you didn't rape her?

09:37.945 --> 09:39.411
Oh...

09:39.413 --> 09:40.779
Hollis loves him some women.

09:40.781 --> 09:42.347
And, boy,
do women love them some Hollis.

09:42.349 --> 09:44.849
In all my years,
not a one of them fillies

09:44.851 --> 09:47.118
ever needed an arm twist
to roll in my hay.

09:47.120 --> 09:49.554
Abby: Are you kidding me?
This can't be.

09:49.556 --> 09:50.922
His numbers went up?

09:50.924 --> 09:52.290
Five points in some polls.

09:52.292 --> 09:53.592
How the hell?

09:53.594 --> 09:54.626
Hollis Doyle's a racist.

09:54.628 --> 09:56.061
Quinn: Yeah, we know that

09:56.063 --> 09:57.862
from every time
he opens his mouth to speak.

09:57.864 --> 10:00.632
Yes, but did you know
that he runs with the KKK?

10:01.935 --> 10:03.969
Hollis Doyle went on
a hunting retreat

10:03.971 --> 10:06.371
with Martin Becker,
Grand Wizard of the KKK.

10:06.373 --> 10:09.708
And not only was he out there
hunting with these pathetic...

10:09.710 --> 10:11.142
Sheet-wearing...

10:11.144 --> 10:13.712
Racists with big guns
and tiny brains.

10:13.714 --> 10:16.247
...he took their money.

10:16.249 --> 10:19.584
$100,000 of money
from the KKK.

10:19.586 --> 10:21.119
Hollis Doyle is...

10:21.121 --> 10:23.154
...the greatest defender
of free speech

10:23.156 --> 10:24.556
this nation has ever seen.

10:24.558 --> 10:26.925
We're not just talking about
free speech here.

10:26.927 --> 10:28.493
We're talking hate speech.
The KKK.

10:28.495 --> 10:29.661
Will you disavow --

10:29.663 --> 10:30.795
Looky here.

10:30.797 --> 10:33.064
Book and thoughts,
they don't hurt people.

10:33.066 --> 10:34.466
Well, maybe books.

10:34.468 --> 10:37.469
But it's the politically-correct
media elite

10:37.471 --> 10:40.338
that really hurts
the people of this country.

10:40.340 --> 10:42.674
<i> That's keeping all the money</i>
<i> for their judgy,</i>

10:42.676 --> 10:44.843
<i> greedy, over-educated selves.</i>
-Do you hear this?

10:44.845 --> 10:46.578
You're looking
at the front-runner

10:46.580 --> 10:47.812
of the Republican
nomination.

10:47.814 --> 10:48.980
This is
an opportunity.

10:48.982 --> 10:50.949
Now, I know this steps
outside of our strategy,

10:50.951 --> 10:52.117
but I feel that we --

10:52.119 --> 10:53.785
-What do you suggest?
-A news conference.

10:53.787 --> 10:54.986
To prove
what we already know?

10:54.988 --> 10:56.655
That Hollis Doyle
is a xenophobic,

10:56.657 --> 10:58.757
idiotic,
misogynistic racist?

10:58.759 --> 11:00.525
I'm a black man
running for President.

11:00.527 --> 11:02.927
People, my supporters,
are beginning to wonder

11:02.929 --> 11:04.796
why I'm not out there
saying anything.

11:04.798 --> 11:07.298
Your instincts are correct.
You want to do what's right.

11:07.300 --> 11:09.167
You want to lead
those people.
Yes.

11:09.169 --> 11:11.269
Stand up for what you believe
in. Stand up to the bully.

11:11.271 --> 11:13.938
-Yes!
-Those supporters of yours

11:13.940 --> 11:16.641
are begging for you
to do just that.

11:16.643 --> 11:19.844
But they're the ones who think
that you'll be their President.

11:21.314 --> 11:22.814
You feel me, brother?

11:22.816 --> 11:24.716
Mm.

11:24.718 --> 11:26.217
[ Chuckles ]

11:26.219 --> 11:28.787
This is America.

11:28.789 --> 11:31.356
You have another crop
of supporters.

11:31.358 --> 11:32.724
A larger crop.

11:32.726 --> 11:35.293
Much larger, paler crop.

11:35.295 --> 11:39.831
Those supporters, they are okay,
pleased, in fact,

11:39.833 --> 11:41.533
at the idea
of a black president.

11:41.535 --> 11:42.901
As long as
he's not too black.

11:42.903 --> 11:44.202
As long as
he understands his place.

11:44.204 --> 11:46.304
As long as they can be sure
that he's not gonna run

11:46.306 --> 11:48.673
north of the Mason-Dixon
at the first sign of daylight.

11:48.675 --> 11:51.743
See, that is what they'll think
if you stand on the podium

11:51.745 --> 11:53.411
talking about Hollis Doyle

11:53.413 --> 11:55.413
and quoting Rosa Parks
and Huey Newton.

11:55.415 --> 11:58.216
That is an incredibly
simplistic view, Rowan.

11:58.218 --> 12:00.852
Race is nothing more
than a social construct.

12:00.854 --> 12:02.554
And as a man who wants to
lead this country,

12:02.556 --> 12:04.322
I have a moral responsibility
to these --

12:04.324 --> 12:07.559
You need to cease talking.
"Race is a social construct."

12:07.561 --> 12:09.594
You're speaking to a man
from the ghetto.

12:09.596 --> 12:11.996
You have no idea
what you're talking about,

12:11.998 --> 12:14.699
you privileged,
little Ink Well prep school

12:14.701 --> 12:16.768
Ivy League doctor's son.

12:16.770 --> 12:19.104
You ain't no Jesse Jackson.
You ain't got nothing to preach.

12:19.106 --> 12:20.538
You ain't got nothing
to say.

12:20.540 --> 12:21.773
You don't have a dream,

12:21.775 --> 12:23.675
and you have not been
to the mountaintop.

12:23.677 --> 12:25.009
Which is why I chose you.

12:25.011 --> 12:27.011
You gon' be
our first black president.

12:27.013 --> 12:29.080
And you're gonna get there

12:29.082 --> 12:32.117
by making everyone forget
that you are black.

12:32.119 --> 12:34.452
You're going to wait.
Your time will come.

12:34.454 --> 12:37.355
When you are in the Oval,
you can say whatever you want.

12:37.357 --> 12:40.024
Until then, stand still

12:40.026 --> 12:45.697
and hope nobody notices
that this ain't no tan.

12:47.234 --> 12:49.100
Don't make me angry.

12:49.102 --> 12:52.470
♪♪

13:03.083 --> 13:05.083
So...

13:05.085 --> 13:08.153
maybe it's smarter to let
the Republicans go after Hollis.

13:08.155 --> 13:09.788
[ Chuckles ]
That's the brilliant man

13:09.790 --> 13:11.990
that's gonna lead us
to economic prosperity.

13:11.992 --> 13:14.459
Good thinking.
Let the Republicans at him.

13:14.461 --> 13:15.927
Right. Right.

13:15.929 --> 13:17.962
Why should I get my hands dirty
in their mess?

13:17.964 --> 13:19.831
Exactly.

13:19.833 --> 13:22.133
Did you, uh, come up
with your short list

13:22.135 --> 13:24.669
of, uh, possible
Vice Presidential candidates?

13:24.671 --> 13:25.904
-I have some names.
-Good.

13:25.906 --> 13:27.172
I want you to add one more
to the very top.

13:27.174 --> 13:28.640
Jake Ballard.

13:28.642 --> 13:30.275
-Jake Ballard?
-Mm-hmm.

13:30.277 --> 13:31.075
The one who's always at this
house for dinner Jake Ballard?

13:31.077 --> 13:32.844
NSA Chief.

13:32.846 --> 13:34.145
Young, white, handsome.

13:34.147 --> 13:35.980
Name recognition
through the roof

13:35.982 --> 13:37.916
after his marriage
to Vanessa Moss.

13:37.918 --> 13:40.518
I don't know
if that's a good idea.

13:40.520 --> 13:43.555
♪♪

13:48.094 --> 13:49.861
The decision is yours.
You are the candidate.

13:53.800 --> 13:55.600
-Where are we?
-Nowhere.

13:55.602 --> 13:57.769
Hollis isn't a candidate.
He's a rockstar.

13:57.771 --> 13:59.137
I mean,
we can't touch the guy.

13:59.139 --> 14:00.772
[ Sighs ]

14:06.680 --> 14:08.680
Why don't we go after
Hollis' stance on abortion?

14:08.682 --> 14:09.981
Abortion?

14:09.983 --> 14:10.882
Yes.

14:10.884 --> 14:11.983
What would we go after?

14:11.985 --> 14:13.351
He's anti-choice
in an anti-choice party.

14:13.353 --> 14:15.653
-But what if he's not?
-You mean his personal life?

14:15.655 --> 14:16.955
-Yes.
-Do you know something?

14:16.957 --> 14:18.790
I know
that one of his mistresses --

14:18.792 --> 14:20.725
Here's the problem.
We expose him as a hypocrite.

14:20.727 --> 14:22.327
Which I like.
That's effective.

14:22.329 --> 14:23.328
But not with abortion.

14:23.330 --> 14:25.029
To the conservatives
in this party,

14:25.031 --> 14:27.298
it only matters what he<i> says</i>
about abortion, how he votes.

14:27.300 --> 14:29.834
And if he says the right things
and votes the right way --

14:29.836 --> 14:32.036
and he has and he will --
they will forgive him his sins.

14:32.038 --> 14:33.571
If anything,
he could use this

14:33.573 --> 14:35.406
to bolster his standing
with conservatives.

14:35.408 --> 14:37.542
A sinner saved.
Redeemed. No.

14:37.544 --> 14:40.245
Any discussion of abortion
in the primary

14:40.247 --> 14:42.046
will only hurt Mellie,
who says the wrong things

14:42.048 --> 14:44.048
and votes the wrong way
and is tolerated on this issue

14:44.050 --> 14:46.184
only because of everything else
she brings to the party.

14:46.186 --> 14:48.219
But God forbid
they turn around

14:48.221 --> 14:50.388
and find anything
in her history...

14:52.158 --> 14:53.558
An abortion
won't destroy Hollis,

14:53.560 --> 14:54.726
but it could destroy
Mellie.

14:54.728 --> 14:56.828
Quinn!

14:56.830 --> 14:58.263
Turn that up.

14:58.265 --> 15:00.798
Sally:<i> Tell me, Hollis, are you</i>
<i> angry at the mudslinging</i>

15:00.800 --> 15:03.001
<i> that's coming out</i>
<i> of your opponents' camps?</i>

15:03.003 --> 15:04.869
Hollis:<i> Nah.</i>
<i> They're running out of time.</i>

15:04.871 --> 15:07.171
<i> It's like being a 40-year-old</i>
<i> woman without a husband.</i>

15:07.173 --> 15:09.507
<i>You don't say you're desperate,</i>
<i> but you are.</i>
Ugh.

15:09.509 --> 15:11.175
<i> In fact, to show that ol'</i>
<i> Hollis ain't got</i>

15:11.177 --> 15:12.610
<i> no hard feelings,</i>

15:12.612 --> 15:14.946
I'm gonna say right here
and right now

15:14.948 --> 15:17.415
that whichever one of them
gals drops out first

15:17.417 --> 15:18.549
will be my Vice President.

15:18.551 --> 15:20.051
<i> You can't be serious.</i>

15:20.053 --> 15:22.520
<i> I'm as serious as</i>
<i> a fat kid on Halloween.</i>

15:22.522 --> 15:24.956
-Can you believe this?
-I should run for President.

15:24.958 --> 15:26.557
-Disgusting.
-Yeah.

15:26.559 --> 15:28.359
<i> The way I see it,</i>
<i>they've only got two choices --</i>

15:28.361 --> 15:29.894
<i> hitch their wagon</i>
<i> to the Hollis train or lose.</i>

15:29.896 --> 15:31.529
<i> If Susan and Mellie</i>
<i> think they can reach</i>

15:31.531 --> 15:33.298
<i> the White House</i>
<i> by some other means...</i>

15:33.300 --> 15:35.300
<i>Well, As they say, denial ain't</i>
<i> just a river in Egypt.</i>

15:39.873 --> 15:41.072
He can't be serious.

15:41.074 --> 15:42.941
This is not the way
you pick a Vice President.

15:44.878 --> 15:46.210
Maybe we should consider it.

15:46.212 --> 15:47.545
Joining
Hollis Doyle's ticket?

15:47.547 --> 15:49.480
We're down 140 delegates.

15:49.482 --> 15:51.549
-You can't be serious.
-Hollis could win.

15:51.551 --> 15:53.251
He's not going to win.

15:53.253 --> 15:54.152
He<i> could</i> win.

15:54.154 --> 15:56.554
And then we'll be left
with nothing.

15:56.556 --> 15:58.990
We'll be left with our pride.
Our sanity.

15:58.992 --> 16:01.092
Our standards.
Our intellects.

16:01.094 --> 16:02.961
Our humanity.
Our souls.

16:02.963 --> 16:05.229
We need to take Hollis' Veep
deal before Mellie takes it.

16:05.231 --> 16:06.898
Liv and I have agreed
to a cease-fire.

16:06.900 --> 16:08.466
And the cease-fire holds,
Liz.

16:08.468 --> 16:09.968
Nobody is taking that deal.

16:09.970 --> 16:12.070
We're running
for President.

16:12.072 --> 16:14.572
We need to focus everything
we've got on taking down Hollis.

16:14.574 --> 16:15.873
So you don't want to know
what I have on Mellie Grant?

16:22.248 --> 16:23.848
This is it?
Mellie saw a psychic?

16:23.850 --> 16:25.683
12 times.
In the White House.

16:25.685 --> 16:27.585
Yeah,
after her son was killed.

16:27.587 --> 16:29.988
She was trying
to talk to her dead son.

16:29.990 --> 16:32.123
Mellie wants to be
Commander in Chief.

16:32.125 --> 16:34.492
The Commander in Chief
sends America's

16:34.494 --> 16:35.994
sons and daughters into war,

16:35.996 --> 16:38.129
and sometimes
those children die.

16:38.131 --> 16:40.832
How many of their parents
shuffle around in bathrobes

16:40.834 --> 16:43.601
eating fried chicken and trying
to commune with the dead?

16:43.603 --> 16:44.836
They get back to work.

16:44.838 --> 16:47.205
This makes Mellie
seem indulgent and crazy

16:47.207 --> 16:48.873
and unfit for the office.

16:48.875 --> 16:50.341
It makes her seem human.

16:50.343 --> 16:52.677
And it's embarrassing
at the very worst.

16:52.679 --> 16:54.545
It will never
be enough to stop her.

16:54.547 --> 16:55.880
It'll have to be.

16:55.882 --> 16:57.682
Because that is
the best we've got.

16:57.684 --> 17:00.551
It's the only thing
we've got.

17:03.556 --> 17:04.689
[ Door closes ]

17:04.691 --> 17:07.058
♪♪

17:07.060 --> 17:09.527
[ Sighs ]

17:16.202 --> 17:18.703
[ Sighs ]

17:20.306 --> 17:22.740
Being Vice President
wouldn't be so bad.

17:22.742 --> 17:24.709
At least you're
that much closer to the Oval.

17:24.711 --> 17:25.877
Maybe I should take it.

17:25.879 --> 17:28.246
Mellie,
you are going to win.

17:28.248 --> 17:29.480
[ Sighs ]

17:29.482 --> 17:31.182
You have
amazing policy ideas.

17:31.184 --> 17:32.917
You have experience
and vision.

17:32.919 --> 17:34.986
The people of this country
need you.

17:34.988 --> 17:38.890
So I don't want to hear
this crap, okay?

17:38.892 --> 17:40.758
Okay.

17:40.760 --> 17:42.226
Good.

17:42.228 --> 17:44.162
Read the last paragraph
on this page

17:44.164 --> 17:45.496
and tell me what you think.

17:47.167 --> 17:48.666
Thanks.

17:48.668 --> 17:50.068
Anytime.

17:52.672 --> 17:56.674
[ Elevator bell dings ]

17:56.676 --> 17:58.142
Olivia: [ Sighs ]

17:59.379 --> 18:00.978
Move away from my door.

18:00.980 --> 18:03.448
You seem to believe
that there is some finality

18:03.450 --> 18:04.615
to our relationship.

18:04.617 --> 18:06.617
There is not.
I am your father.

18:06.619 --> 18:08.753
Even when I'm dead and buried,
you are me.

18:08.755 --> 18:09.854
What do you want?

18:09.856 --> 18:11.589
To tell you to take the deal.
Hollis' deal.

18:11.591 --> 18:14.292
-Why would I do that?
-Because it's your best option.

18:14.294 --> 18:16.861
You'd just rather face Hollis
in the general.

18:16.863 --> 18:19.063
You'd never admit it,
but Mellie scares you.

18:19.065 --> 18:21.032
I scare you.

18:21.034 --> 18:23.201
Mm.

18:23.203 --> 18:24.802
Take the deal.

18:24.804 --> 18:28.606
Or else your pal
Abby Whelan will.

18:33.213 --> 18:34.579
What do you know?

18:34.581 --> 18:36.280
She's not to be trusted.

18:36.282 --> 18:39.117
She will use your friendship
to disarm you, to soften you up.

18:39.119 --> 18:40.985
And before you feel
the cold steel on your skin,

18:40.987 --> 18:42.787
she will slit your throat.

18:42.789 --> 18:45.056
[ Laughs ]
This isn't going to work.

18:45.058 --> 18:47.024
You don't believe me.

18:48.561 --> 18:51.329
It's okay

18:51.331 --> 18:52.830
if you don't trust me,
Olivia.

18:52.832 --> 18:54.265
It's the fact
that you're willing

18:54.267 --> 18:58.603
to trust anyone but yourself
that I find truly troubling.

18:58.605 --> 19:01.372
[ Elevator bell dings ]

19:03.977 --> 19:06.511
Take the deal.

19:10.483 --> 19:12.116
[<i> Camera shutter clicks</i> ]

19:12.118 --> 19:14.519
We've had limited interaction
since you took over at the NSA,

19:14.521 --> 19:16.087
but, uh,
it's always been positive.

19:16.089 --> 19:16.988
I'd say so.

19:16.990 --> 19:18.623
You're a reasonable guy.

19:18.625 --> 19:20.091
Am I?

19:20.093 --> 19:21.526
I mean, you don't actually
know me at all.

19:21.528 --> 19:23.528
That's why
I called this meeting.

19:23.530 --> 19:25.129
To get to know me.

19:25.131 --> 19:27.865
No.
Out of courtesy.

19:27.867 --> 19:29.200
To tell you man to man

19:29.202 --> 19:31.035
that I won't be considering you
for Vice President.

19:31.037 --> 19:33.137
I have some other people
with more experience

19:33.139 --> 19:35.106
who better balance the ticket
electorally.

19:35.108 --> 19:36.107
Mm. No.

19:37.710 --> 19:38.543
What?

19:38.545 --> 19:39.877
Look,
you're a stand-up guy,

19:39.879 --> 19:41.546
so I'll be straight
with you.

19:41.548 --> 19:43.214
I'm not
a reasonable man.

19:43.216 --> 19:44.215
What is this?

19:44.217 --> 19:46.484
That's it.
Right there.

19:46.486 --> 19:50.321
That is why he chose you.

19:50.323 --> 19:51.656
Because you'd still ask
the question

19:51.658 --> 19:53.124
when it's plain
as God's blue sky.

19:53.126 --> 19:55.993
You have no choice here.
You know you have no choice.

19:55.995 --> 19:59.030
But yet your brain
can't compute it.

19:59.032 --> 20:00.131
You're --

20:00.133 --> 20:02.900
Well, it's charming.

20:02.902 --> 20:05.136
I think
this meeting is ov--
I am your Vice President.

20:05.138 --> 20:07.905
And Eli and I will drag your
tired ass to the White House,

20:07.907 --> 20:09.974
and you will smile and wave
and wait for us

20:09.976 --> 20:11.542
to turn you on and off
and changes your batteries.

20:11.544 --> 20:13.978
Okay?

20:13.980 --> 20:16.147
No.

20:16.149 --> 20:18.416
What if I say no?

20:19.719 --> 20:21.586
Remember the car accident
you had

20:21.588 --> 20:23.354
after Liv introduced you
to her dad?

20:23.356 --> 20:27.058
The one that shattered
your entire body.

20:28.361 --> 20:30.595
That wasn't an accident.

20:30.597 --> 20:32.430
That was me.

20:33.533 --> 20:35.399
Don't say no to me.

20:42.508 --> 20:45.276
[ Sighs ]

20:47.380 --> 20:49.914
[ Door opens ]

20:49.916 --> 20:51.382
[ Door closes ]

20:51.384 --> 20:53.217
Howdy, darlin'.

20:53.219 --> 20:55.519
Hollis.

20:57.590 --> 20:59.190
[ Sighs ]

20:59.192 --> 21:00.958
I always knew
you were the smart one.

21:00.960 --> 21:02.360
I want Mellie Grant
on that ticket.

21:02.362 --> 21:05.229
Oh, so do I.
So do I.

21:05.231 --> 21:06.964
Classy piece of ass,
that lady.

21:06.966 --> 21:08.466
Elevates us both.

21:08.468 --> 21:10.968
However, we do have some serious
concerns about your message.

21:10.970 --> 21:14.372
It's exclusionary,
and deeply offensive.

21:14.374 --> 21:15.873
Oh, hell,
you don't think I believe

21:15.875 --> 21:17.275
any of that racist crap
I spew out there

21:17.277 --> 21:18.609
in the boonies, do you?
[ Scoffs ]

21:18.611 --> 21:20.378
I'm a businessman,
Livvie.

21:20.380 --> 21:23.247
Just giving the customers
what they want.

21:23.249 --> 21:25.316
And you thinking I'm some kind
of deep-fried cross burner

21:25.318 --> 21:27.084
'cause I'm from south
of the Mason-Dixon

21:27.086 --> 21:28.819
ain't exactly open-minded,
you don't mind me saying.

21:31.758 --> 21:34.292
[ Chuckles ]
Personal beliefs aside,

21:34.294 --> 21:36.594
your speeches,
your rhetoric --

21:36.596 --> 21:38.829
Is for a specific market.

21:38.831 --> 21:40.564
And when I get
to the general,

21:40.566 --> 21:42.300
all them
mouth-breathing morons

21:42.302 --> 21:43.834
who couldn't read a newspaper
column

21:43.836 --> 21:45.970
if their lives depended on it,
well, they'll think I only

21:45.972 --> 21:48.172
just started telling people
what they wanted to hear,

21:48.174 --> 21:50.074
and they got the real me
six months ago.

21:50.076 --> 21:52.610
To tell you the truth,
my most pressing concern is

21:52.612 --> 21:54.345
there ain't enough Purell
in the world

21:54.347 --> 21:56.847
to make me want to keep shaking
their filthy, inbred hands.

21:56.849 --> 21:59.650
I mean -- ugh! --
country people.

21:59.652 --> 22:00.818
Am I right?

22:00.820 --> 22:02.320
[ Chuckles ]

22:02.322 --> 22:03.287
So, we got a deal?

22:03.289 --> 22:05.022
We got a deal.

22:06.626 --> 22:07.692
Now see this?

22:07.694 --> 22:10.628
You,
I got no problem with.

22:10.630 --> 22:12.863
Mm.
[ Chuckles ]

22:17.470 --> 22:19.103
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

22:20.373 --> 22:22.139
I've been waiting here an hour.
I have meetings.

22:22.141 --> 22:24.508
I do run a country.
Where have you been?

22:24.510 --> 22:25.643
I went to see Hollis.

22:25.645 --> 22:27.111
-You what?!
-Behind my back?

22:27.113 --> 22:29.347
You took him up
on his totally offensive --

22:29.349 --> 22:32.016
Quinn: Mellie cannot be
Hollis Doyle's VP.

22:32.018 --> 22:33.317
Over my dead body.

22:33.319 --> 22:34.618
Quinn. It's okay.

22:34.620 --> 22:37.054
-How is any of this okay?
-I went to see Hollis.

22:37.056 --> 22:39.490
And then I went to share
some truth, like a good

22:39.492 --> 22:41.792
[As Sally Langston]
"Lovah of Liberty."

22:41.794 --> 22:44.161
And I just thank the good Lord
every day

22:44.163 --> 22:47.131
for all the wonderful people
in America's small towns

22:47.133 --> 22:49.500
who come out to see me
day in, day out.

22:49.502 --> 22:54.238
Their support, it means
the world to me, truth be told.

22:54.240 --> 22:56.240
Hmm. Really?

22:56.242 --> 22:58.476
Because I've heard the truth is
actually a bit different.

22:58.478 --> 23:00.811
[ Laughs ] I don't know
what you're hearing, but, uh...

23:00.813 --> 23:03.214
<i> There ain't enough Purell</i>
<i> in the world</i>

23:03.216 --> 23:06.217
<i>to make me want to keep shaking</i>
<i> their filthy, inbred hands.</i>

23:06.219 --> 23:09.920
<i> I mean, country people.</i>
<i> Am I right?</i>

23:09.922 --> 23:12.790
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

23:19.098 --> 23:20.531
That is
taken out of context.

23:20.533 --> 23:21.832
-It is?
-That's right.

23:21.834 --> 23:22.933
Because I remember
what I said --

23:22.935 --> 23:24.835
Because this is
what you said right before.

23:24.837 --> 23:26.937
<i> You don't think I believe</i>
<i> any of that racist crap</i>

23:26.939 --> 23:29.206
<i> I spew out there</i>
<i> in the boonies, do you?</i>

23:29.208 --> 23:31.208
So if I'm misunderstanding
something, Mr. Doyle,

23:31.210 --> 23:32.877
please feel free
to set me straight.

23:32.879 --> 23:34.912
Because it sounds
to this country girl

23:34.914 --> 23:37.581
like you are making a mockery
of the voters, and by extension,

23:37.583 --> 23:39.450
the United States of America
as a whole.

23:39.452 --> 23:41.085
Care to comment,
Mr. Doyle?

23:41.087 --> 23:42.686
Mnh-mnh.
[ Clears throat ] Uh...

23:42.688 --> 23:44.722
It's not the first time
we've seen a campaign

23:44.724 --> 23:47.224
spontaneously combust
on the primary trail

23:47.226 --> 23:49.527
due to a singe
watershed incident.

23:49.529 --> 23:51.562
WOMAN:
You're a liar, Hollis!

23:51.564 --> 23:54.131
Hollis, has your entire campaign
been a fraud?

23:54.133 --> 23:55.466
No comment.

23:55.468 --> 23:57.034
Hollis!
Hollis!

23:57.036 --> 24:00.738
What about the allegations
of racism and rape?

24:00.740 --> 24:03.774
Insiders agree it won't be long
before Mr. Doyle

24:03.776 --> 24:05.443
is forced
to pull out of the race.

24:05.445 --> 24:06.911
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

24:06.913 --> 24:09.246
[ Both laughing ]

24:09.248 --> 24:12.216
So, how long do you think
before he suspends his campaign?

24:12.218 --> 24:14.585
At the rate his donors
are dropping out,

24:14.587 --> 24:17.087
I'd say 24 hours
at the most.

24:17.089 --> 24:19.223
[ Both laugh ]

24:19.225 --> 24:20.724
[ Sighs ]

24:20.726 --> 24:23.060
So, in 24 hours,
Hollis will be out of the race,

24:23.062 --> 24:25.896
and we won't be fighting
on the same side anymore.

24:25.898 --> 24:27.398
No. Tomorrow we go
back in the ring.

24:27.400 --> 24:28.899
Mellie versus Susan.

24:28.901 --> 24:29.900
Enemies again.

24:29.902 --> 24:31.669
Enemies again.

24:38.311 --> 24:39.777
Hey, it was fun
while it lasted.

24:39.779 --> 24:41.512
It was.

24:42.682 --> 24:44.448
Abby.

24:44.450 --> 24:45.749
I'm not going to hold back.

24:45.751 --> 24:46.851
Oh, you shouldn't.

24:46.853 --> 24:48.853
Because I want the pleasure
of beating you

24:48.855 --> 24:49.954
when you're running
full speed.

24:49.956 --> 24:51.755
Let's go then.

24:51.757 --> 24:54.525
Liz, it's me.
Let's get everyone together.

24:54.527 --> 24:57.595
♪♪

24:59.332 --> 25:01.165
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

25:07.306 --> 25:09.340
The view is much better
from the Truman.

25:09.342 --> 25:11.509
[ Door closes ]

25:11.511 --> 25:13.177
I don't know if I would
call this an honor,

25:13.179 --> 25:14.879
but I am surprised
to see you.

25:18.718 --> 25:21.051
I respect you, Edison.

25:21.053 --> 25:23.821
By this town's standards,
you should be canonized.

25:23.823 --> 25:25.122
I don't need your pep talk,
Olivia.

25:25.124 --> 25:26.290
Check the numbers.

25:26.292 --> 25:27.725
I'm two-thirds of the way
to the nomination.

25:27.727 --> 25:29.894
And I would be happy for you
if I thought there was a chance

25:29.896 --> 25:31.328
that you might actually
run the country.

25:31.330 --> 25:32.730
-I'm the favorite.
-You may win.

25:32.732 --> 25:35.533
You may be sworn in
as President.

25:35.535 --> 25:37.701
But you will not
be running the country.

25:37.703 --> 25:39.136
My father will.

25:39.138 --> 25:41.205
Is that all, Olivia?

25:41.207 --> 25:42.506
Michigan.

25:42.508 --> 25:44.241
You were down six points
the night before the primary.

25:44.243 --> 25:45.543
You win by three.

25:45.545 --> 25:47.011
Ohio, same thing.

25:47.013 --> 25:48.178
Idaho caucus.

25:48.180 --> 25:49.847
Statistical tie going in.

25:49.849 --> 25:52.182
Do you see a pattern?

25:52.184 --> 25:53.384
[ Sighs ]

25:53.386 --> 25:56.720
My father is stealing
this election for you.

25:56.722 --> 25:58.722
Not because
he believes in you.

25:58.724 --> 26:01.692
Not because he wants to
lay history at your feet.

26:01.694 --> 26:03.994
He's doing it because he thinks
you're easy to control.

26:03.996 --> 26:05.829
I wonder where he could have
gotten that idea?

26:05.831 --> 26:07.264
You can make this about me
if you want --

26:07.266 --> 26:08.399
It's<i> always</i> about you,

26:08.401 --> 26:10.067
whether I'm the one
making it or not.

26:10.069 --> 26:12.069
Has he suggested Jake Ballard
as your running mate yet?

26:14.440 --> 26:16.540
[ Scoffs ]

26:16.542 --> 26:19.777
♪♪

26:23.115 --> 26:25.849
I am this close
to the White House.

26:25.851 --> 26:27.551
Not like this.

26:27.553 --> 26:29.453
You need to drop out.

26:29.455 --> 26:31.922
And find out what it means
to say no to your father?

26:31.924 --> 26:32.957
I can help you.

26:32.959 --> 26:34.058
I can get you
out of this race

26:34.060 --> 26:35.392
and make sure
that you have a real shot

26:35.394 --> 26:36.894
at the presidency
in the next frame.

26:36.896 --> 26:38.195
How?

26:38.197 --> 26:41.565
By saying everything
you've ever wanted to say

26:41.567 --> 26:42.967
about Hollis Doyle.

26:45.371 --> 26:46.971
The polls had you
beating Hollis Doyle

26:46.973 --> 26:48.072
in the general election.

26:48.074 --> 26:49.306
You happy to see him gone?

26:49.308 --> 26:51.308
[ Chuckles ] I'm running against
Frankie Vargas.

26:51.310 --> 26:52.443
Not Hollis Doyle.

26:52.445 --> 26:53.944
Thank you.
I have to prepare for my speech.

26:53.946 --> 26:56.246
I find it hard to believe
that as a black man

26:56.248 --> 26:58.616
running for president, you have
no opinion on the matter.

26:58.618 --> 27:03.053
You want a sound bite?
You want the truth?

27:03.055 --> 27:06.457
Hollis Doyle is
a disgusting piece of trash.

27:06.459 --> 27:07.725
A relic.

27:07.727 --> 27:09.293
A man,
like many other white men,

27:09.295 --> 27:11.929
who have had a free run
at prosperity and opportunity.

27:11.931 --> 27:13.230
For whom discrimination
and injustice

27:13.232 --> 27:14.932
are as foreign to them
as the Muslim immigrants

27:14.934 --> 27:17.101
that they want to ban
from our country.

27:17.103 --> 27:19.837
And now that they don't have
a free run, they're lashing out.

27:19.839 --> 27:21.905
To be honest, I can't believe
it took him explicitly

27:21.907 --> 27:23.974
expressing his racism
for you all to start

27:23.976 --> 27:25.976
asking these damn questions.

27:25.978 --> 27:28.612
He ends every speech with
"Dare to be great again."

27:28.614 --> 27:30.414
Huh? What?

27:30.416 --> 27:33.283
Should we return to slavery?
Jim Crow?

27:33.285 --> 27:35.853
In today's America,
my gay friends can get married.

27:35.855 --> 27:38.288
In today's America,
I can vote.

27:38.290 --> 27:40.090
50 years ago --
in Hollis Doyle's lifetime --

27:40.092 --> 27:41.759
that wasn't the case.

27:41.761 --> 27:44.161
In today's America,
my parents don't have to

27:44.163 --> 27:46.330
recruit a white couple
who worked alongside them

27:46.332 --> 27:48.098
at the cereal plant
to apply for a mortgage

27:48.100 --> 27:50.334
because banks wouldn't lend
to folks with brown skin.

27:50.336 --> 27:52.536
In today's America,
we have the Brandon Bill,

27:52.538 --> 27:54.872
which means I may not have to
tell my future son

27:54.874 --> 27:57.007
that he could be murdered
by law enforcement

27:57.009 --> 27:59.176
just for asking
why he was pulled over.

27:59.178 --> 28:00.978
Black lives do matter

28:00.980 --> 28:04.014
because young black people
are under attack.

28:04.016 --> 28:05.883
Immigrants, too.

28:05.885 --> 28:08.185
The fact that Doyle insists
on saying "all lives matter"

28:08.187 --> 28:11.155
when talking about this movement
really pisses me off.

28:11.157 --> 28:13.123
It's like walking up
into someone else's funeral

28:13.125 --> 28:17.227
and screaming, "Why are you not
crying for my daddy?

28:17.229 --> 28:19.329
He's dead, too."

28:19.331 --> 28:22.066
Well, yes, he is.
And that is sad.

28:22.068 --> 28:24.168
But that is not the topic
of the conversation.

28:24.170 --> 28:26.370
Go stand over there
and let the adults talk.

28:26.372 --> 28:29.506
Hollis Doyle is a thug.
A punk.

28:29.508 --> 28:31.542
And the people who support him
are thugs or punks.

28:31.544 --> 28:33.143
Or they condone his behavior.

28:33.145 --> 28:35.579
They are not Americans.

28:35.581 --> 28:39.183
The idea that this country
belongs to one kind of person

28:39.185 --> 28:42.986
is the least American idea
that anyone has ever had.

28:42.988 --> 28:46.156
In fact, it is the opposite
of the ideals of this nation.

28:46.158 --> 28:47.725
Nothing needs to be restored.

28:47.727 --> 28:49.727
Nothing needs to
be made great again.

28:49.729 --> 28:52.196
We are a better nation
than we were 20 years ago.

28:52.198 --> 28:54.898
Than we were 50 years ago.
Than we were 100 years ago.

28:54.900 --> 28:57.067
Than we were at our founding.

28:57.069 --> 28:59.436
That is the point of America.

28:59.438 --> 29:03.107
We are a country where we are
always greater than our past.

29:03.109 --> 29:05.843
I am proud to live in a nation
where a black man

29:05.845 --> 29:08.078
has a legitimate shot
at the White House.

29:08.080 --> 29:10.214
<i> That's</i> American greatness.

29:10.216 --> 29:12.549
[ All murmuring ]

29:12.551 --> 29:14.651
He just lost the presidency.

29:22.428 --> 29:23.927
<i> And there you have it, folks.</i>

29:23.929 --> 29:25.562
<i> Raw, passionate words</i>
<i> from Senator Edison Davis.</i>

29:25.564 --> 29:28.065
<i> The kind of unfiltered talk</i>
<i> we are not accustomed</i>

29:28.067 --> 29:30.067
<i> to hearing</i>
<i> from a presidential hopeful.</i>

29:30.069 --> 29:31.969
<i> You have to wonder</i>
<i> how voters will respond.</i>

29:31.971 --> 29:34.738
[ Sighs ] Do you really have to
wonder, Angela?

29:34.740 --> 29:36.240
I thought I told you
to put the fear of God,

29:36.242 --> 29:37.274
the fear of<i> me</i> in him.

29:37.276 --> 29:38.776
Trust me.
I followed orders.

29:38.778 --> 29:40.711
Then how do you explain
the man self-immolating

29:40.713 --> 29:42.579
on live television.

29:42.581 --> 29:44.481
I don't.

29:47.386 --> 29:48.585
You know, Senator, you, uh,

29:48.587 --> 29:50.420
you spoke for a lot of people
in this country.

29:50.422 --> 29:52.756
Come on, concede!
Come on, you son of a --

29:52.758 --> 29:55.459
[ Sighs ]

29:55.461 --> 29:57.394
Conceding?
Not conceding? What?

29:57.396 --> 29:59.596
[ Quietly ] Conceding.

29:59.598 --> 30:02.666
[ Muted cheers ]

30:05.237 --> 30:07.337
Well,
I'm sorry to hear that.

30:07.339 --> 30:09.273
Okay.

30:09.275 --> 30:11.241
Thank you, Senator.

30:11.243 --> 30:12.643
[ Drums on desk ]

30:12.645 --> 30:14.645
[ Cheers and applause ]

30:14.647 --> 30:16.180
This is
really happening, Cyrus.

30:16.182 --> 30:18.248
Congratulations,
Governor Vargas.

30:18.250 --> 30:20.284
[ Scoffs ]
You're the Democratic nominee

30:20.286 --> 30:22.286
for the President
of the United States.

30:22.288 --> 30:23.654
[ Cheering ]

30:23.656 --> 30:25.189
Oh!

30:25.191 --> 30:27.357
[ Laughs ]

30:27.359 --> 30:28.692
-Yeah!
-Ha!

30:28.694 --> 30:30.460
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

30:30.462 --> 30:32.095
Cyrus:
Why'd you change your mind?

30:32.097 --> 30:35.499
Because even when he's running
full speed, I'm running faster.

30:35.501 --> 30:38.101
I don't know what that means,
but may I say how glad I am

30:38.103 --> 30:40.103
that you have chosen
to never go to therapy?

30:40.105 --> 30:41.538
It has served us so well.

30:41.540 --> 30:43.106
Cyrus, got to go.

30:43.108 --> 30:44.775
You confirm
the dirt on Susan?

30:44.777 --> 30:45.843
It's as bad as we thought.

30:45.845 --> 30:47.778
Oh, not bad meaning bad.
Bad meaning good.

30:47.780 --> 30:50.314
Bad meaning really good
for us.

30:50.316 --> 30:52.282
This is enough.

30:52.284 --> 30:54.017
To get Susan to drop out
of the race?

30:54.019 --> 30:56.887
Yeah, it is.

30:56.889 --> 30:59.022
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

31:00.326 --> 31:01.992
Ms. Whelan,
you wanted to see me?

31:01.994 --> 31:03.961
You led Olivia Pope's
Secret Service detail

31:03.963 --> 31:05.495
when she was
in the White House, right?

31:05.497 --> 31:07.331
Yes, ma'am.

31:07.333 --> 31:09.132
The last night she lived
in the White House,

31:09.134 --> 31:10.734
she visited Senator Grant
in the Capitol

31:10.736 --> 31:12.302
during the Senator's
filibuster.

31:12.304 --> 31:13.537
Were you with her
that evening?

31:13.539 --> 31:14.805
Yes, ma'am.

31:14.807 --> 31:15.906
Do you remember
where Miss Pope went

31:15.908 --> 31:17.307
after she left
the Capitol that night?

31:21.080 --> 31:24.214
♪♪

31:37.329 --> 31:38.929
-Liv.
-Abby.

31:38.931 --> 31:40.497
We need to talk.

31:42.268 --> 31:43.500
You have something.

31:43.502 --> 31:45.669
And I'm sure you do, too.

31:45.671 --> 31:47.838
Come to
the White House tonight.

31:47.840 --> 31:49.339
We'll talk.

31:52.711 --> 31:54.611
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

31:57.883 --> 31:59.616
-Olivia Pope is here.
-Send her in.

31:59.618 --> 32:01.018
Oh, she's in the Oval.
Should I --

32:01.020 --> 32:02.386
-Oval?
-Yeah. They all are.

32:02.388 --> 32:04.554
They?!
Who's they?

32:04.556 --> 32:07.791
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:10.262 --> 32:11.762
[ Sighs ]

32:14.066 --> 32:16.133
Olivia,
this was not the plan.

32:16.135 --> 32:18.702
This will only work
if we get everyone on board.

32:18.704 --> 32:20.203
All the players.
From the start.

32:21.941 --> 32:23.874
Fine.

32:23.876 --> 32:25.876
Okay, everyone.

32:25.878 --> 32:28.478
The two campaigns have agreed
to exchange opposition research.

32:28.480 --> 32:30.247
We show you the worst dirt
we have on Susan.

32:30.249 --> 32:32.049
You show us the worst dirt
you have on Mellie.

32:32.051 --> 32:33.650
Tonight, right now,
in front of everybody.

32:33.652 --> 32:34.952
And each side
has a decision to make.

32:34.954 --> 32:36.753
Stay in the race
or get out.

32:36.755 --> 32:38.155
If you decide to stay in,
the dirt will be used

32:38.157 --> 32:40.791
against you publicly.
-And if you decide to get out,

32:40.793 --> 32:42.893
the dirt gets buried
and you leave the race clean,

32:42.895 --> 32:44.461
ready to run another day.

32:44.463 --> 32:46.596
So, this is how
you Republicans do it?

32:46.598 --> 32:48.265
-Any questions?
-Yes. One.

32:48.267 --> 32:49.933
Why the hell
are we doing this?

32:49.935 --> 32:51.335
Because they want one of you
to drop out.

32:51.337 --> 32:52.102
Susan:
I'm not dropping out.

32:52.104 --> 32:53.904
Neither am I.

32:53.906 --> 32:55.305
Well, I'm double
not dropping out.

32:55.307 --> 32:57.441
Did you just call doubles
on not dropping out?

32:57.443 --> 32:58.976
-Yes.
-You should drop out.

32:58.978 --> 33:01.244
Nobody wants anybody
to drop out.

33:01.246 --> 33:02.579
But the fact is,

33:02.581 --> 33:03.914
if you deploy your arsenals
against each other,

33:03.916 --> 33:05.682
you're both gonna get hurt,
one of you mortally.

33:05.684 --> 33:06.950
And the one who survives
will end up losing

33:06.952 --> 33:08.285
to Frankie Vargas anyway.

33:08.287 --> 33:09.987
This is a way for us to pick
the strongest candidate,

33:09.989 --> 33:11.655
protect the one who isn't,

33:11.657 --> 33:13.090
and give the party
the best chance

33:13.092 --> 33:15.192
to win the election
in the fall. It's smart.

33:15.194 --> 33:17.094
How do we know
this is the worst you've got?

33:17.096 --> 33:18.829
Why would we hold something back
at this point?

33:24.136 --> 33:25.669
I'll go first.
Susan --

33:25.671 --> 33:27.437
Wait. Hold on.

33:27.439 --> 33:28.672
I just want to say,

33:28.674 --> 33:29.873
if this is about the thing
with the koala --

33:29.875 --> 33:32.976
It's -- It's not.
Susan, it's about David.

33:32.978 --> 33:34.711
David?

33:34.713 --> 33:36.146
Liv?

33:36.148 --> 33:38.515
Your boyfriend and advisor
agreed to drop

33:38.517 --> 33:41.551
a longstanding investigation
by the Department of Justice

33:41.553 --> 33:44.021
into Tamarac Sugar in exchange
for securing your endorsement

33:44.023 --> 33:45.856
of Governor Baker
in the Florida primary.

33:45.858 --> 33:48.458
It's all there.
-Is that true?

33:48.460 --> 33:50.293
-[ Sighs ]
-Is that true?!

33:50.295 --> 33:52.529
-How could you do this withou--
-How could<i> she</i> do this?!

33:52.531 --> 33:55.599
Are you friggin' serious?!
You lied to me again!

33:57.202 --> 33:58.702
-Here. Here.
-Thank you.

33:58.704 --> 34:00.837
If this is true, Rosen,
I'll be accepting

34:00.839 --> 34:02.506
your resignation
as Attorney General

34:02.508 --> 34:04.074
of the United States
in the morning.

34:04.076 --> 34:06.243
Are you sure you want to
do that, Mr. President?

34:06.245 --> 34:07.811
Putting aside
what it does to your legacy,

34:07.813 --> 34:09.212
if David resigns
because of this,

34:09.214 --> 34:10.914
then Susan has to step down
as Vice President,

34:10.916 --> 34:12.699
and she'll never
become President.

34:12.700 --> 34:14.483
Do you want to ruin<i> her</i> career
for something<i> he</i> did?

34:14.486 --> 34:15.719
I wanted you to win.

34:15.721 --> 34:17.888
Shut up.
Abby, what do you have?

34:17.890 --> 34:19.189
I'm sorry.

34:19.191 --> 34:22.426
♪♪

34:29.201 --> 34:30.901
[ Sighs ]

34:30.903 --> 34:35.338
Mellie hired a psychic
to talk to Jerry after he died.

34:35.340 --> 34:37.207
He was in the White House
a dozen times.

34:37.209 --> 34:38.875
-She was grieving.
-[ Scoffs ]

34:38.877 --> 34:40.210
I don't think
it's fair to use that.

34:40.212 --> 34:41.778
Liv. Abby.

34:41.780 --> 34:43.213
These were the rules,
Mr. President.

34:43.215 --> 34:44.948
It was my son.

34:48.053 --> 34:50.720
Well, at least
we know what we're facing.

34:50.722 --> 34:53.690
♪♪

34:59.431 --> 35:00.597
Where are you going,
Susan?

35:00.599 --> 35:02.199
I'm done.

35:02.201 --> 35:04.367
I quit.

35:04.369 --> 35:06.369
Congratulations, Mellie.

35:06.371 --> 35:09.773
♪♪

35:09.775 --> 35:11.708
[ Door closes ]

35:16.081 --> 35:17.981
You can't quit!
I refuse to let you quit.

35:17.983 --> 35:19.983
That you won't throw
that idiot Rosen under the bus

35:19.985 --> 35:21.952
so you can be the
President of the United States

35:21.954 --> 35:23.820
is ludicrous,
and that's the only word for it.

35:23.822 --> 35:25.989
Liz, every voter in this country
is gonna think

35:25.991 --> 35:27.924
I knew about
that big sugar deal.

35:27.926 --> 35:29.793
Or, if I didn't know,
that I should have.

35:29.795 --> 35:32.062
It's over.
I'm out.

35:34.299 --> 35:35.765
[ Scoffs ]

35:35.767 --> 35:37.367
Ludicrous.

35:41.473 --> 35:42.706
[ Door closes ]

35:48.847 --> 35:50.614
I know
there's nothing I can say.

35:50.616 --> 35:52.015
No.

35:52.017 --> 35:52.983
Or do.

35:52.985 --> 35:54.651
Also no.

35:58.157 --> 36:02.359
I didn't want to do this --
Me run for President.

36:02.361 --> 36:05.262
Sounded...ridiculous.

36:05.264 --> 36:08.098
But you convinced me.

36:08.100 --> 36:12.169
It took you months,
but you convinced me.

36:12.171 --> 36:15.472
You made me want it,
and then you took it away.

36:15.474 --> 36:18.375
You have to believe me
when I say how sorry I am,

36:18.377 --> 36:19.709
and that I know
I screwed up.

36:19.711 --> 36:21.378
But honestly,
I did it for you.

36:21.380 --> 36:23.046
Because I believed in you
so much --

36:23.048 --> 36:24.714
-No, you didn't.
-You know I did.

36:24.716 --> 36:26.283
-Y-You didn't.
-You know I did.

36:26.285 --> 36:27.450
You didn't.

36:27.452 --> 36:28.818
I know you didn't,

36:28.820 --> 36:31.388
because you didn't think
I could do it on my own.

36:31.390 --> 36:34.357
Oh, the worst part is,
if you had believed in me...

36:34.359 --> 36:35.992
You'd still be running
for President.

36:35.994 --> 36:38.128
...I'd still be in love
with you.

36:38.130 --> 36:39.563
Susan, please, I love you.

36:39.565 --> 36:41.131
I think you're amazing.

36:41.133 --> 36:43.300
I know that!

36:43.302 --> 36:46.236
I know I'm amazing.

36:46.238 --> 36:49.506
I'm witty and cute
and funny

36:49.508 --> 36:50.874
and smarter than you.

36:50.876 --> 36:53.076
I'm incredible, David.

36:53.078 --> 36:57.247
I'm gonna change the damn world,
which is why this is over.

36:57.249 --> 37:00.183
I know,
but you don't.

37:00.185 --> 37:02.319
I can't be with someone
who doesn't believe in me.

37:02.321 --> 37:04.154
Whether I'm the President
of the United States

37:04.156 --> 37:07.490
or some substitute teacher
in suburbia somewhere,

37:07.492 --> 37:09.092
I believe in myself,

37:09.094 --> 37:12.596
and I need to be with someone
who feels the same way.

37:14.399 --> 37:16.499
You can go now.

37:16.501 --> 37:18.501
'Cause guess what?

37:18.503 --> 37:21.271
You just got dumped

37:21.273 --> 37:24.541
by the Vice President
of the United States of America,

37:24.543 --> 37:26.810
and she has work to do.

37:31.183 --> 37:34.017
♪♪

37:39.558 --> 37:42.325
[ Crying ]

37:46.632 --> 37:49.566
It is the end of the line
for Susan Ross,

37:49.568 --> 37:51.601
who has announced
that she is suspending

37:51.603 --> 37:53.236
her campaign for the presidency.

37:53.238 --> 37:57.040
Though ahead in some polls,
she attributed the decision

37:57.042 --> 37:59.109
to a vastly diminished
war chest,

37:59.111 --> 38:02.579
a result of her refusal
to court soft-money donors.

38:02.581 --> 38:05.649
[ Camera shutter clicking ]
It is not my time
to be President.

38:05.651 --> 38:07.784
But I have been called upon
to lead

38:07.786 --> 38:09.919
by clearing the field
in this race,

38:09.921 --> 38:12.956
because it is essential
that a Republican be the winner

38:12.958 --> 38:14.491
in the general election.

38:14.493 --> 38:16.893
And that Republican
should be Mellie Grant.

38:20.299 --> 38:21.831
What did I say?

38:21.833 --> 38:22.799
[ Sighs ]

38:22.801 --> 38:24.334
I know, I know.

38:24.336 --> 38:26.336
No.
I want to hear the words.

38:26.338 --> 38:28.305
What did I say?
[ Laughs ]

38:28.307 --> 38:29.673
"Mellie, you can do this.

38:29.675 --> 38:31.007
You will do this.
You will win."

38:31.009 --> 38:32.042
And what happened?

38:33.478 --> 38:34.944
-I won.
-Say what?

38:34.946 --> 38:36.313
I won!

38:36.315 --> 38:37.914
Oh, come on.
A little louder now.

38:37.916 --> 38:39.149
I won!!

38:39.151 --> 38:40.483
[ Laughs ]

38:40.485 --> 38:41.718
Oh!

38:42.954 --> 38:44.321
[ Sighs ]

38:48.960 --> 38:51.461
[ Door opens ]
Mrs. Grant? They are ready
for your interview.

38:51.463 --> 38:53.029
Thank you, Margaret.

38:53.031 --> 38:54.431
[ Clears throat ]

38:54.433 --> 38:56.099
I'll see you after.

38:58.370 --> 39:00.036
[ Camera shutter clicks ]
[ Applause ]

39:00.038 --> 39:03.973
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

39:03.975 --> 39:05.842
Thank you, Madam Vice President.

39:05.844 --> 39:08.044
And thank all of you
for your support.

39:08.046 --> 39:11.047
It's been a long, tough road,
but the journey has just begun.

39:11.049 --> 39:12.816
[ Applause ]

39:12.818 --> 39:15.485
<i> It's time to unite</i>
<i>as citizens of this great land,</i>

39:15.487 --> 39:18.521
<i> and show the world that</i>
<i> the United States of America</i>

39:18.523 --> 39:20.990
<i> is stronger than ever.</i>

39:20.992 --> 39:21.958
[ Applause ]

39:21.960 --> 39:23.026
Wow.

39:23.028 --> 39:25.028
She actually did it.

39:25.030 --> 39:27.964
<i> We</i> actually did it.

39:27.966 --> 39:29.799
True.

39:34.539 --> 39:36.706
For you.
A Bordeaux.

39:36.708 --> 39:38.842
As a consolation prize?

39:38.844 --> 39:39.709
[ Chuckles ]

39:39.711 --> 39:41.578
That would only be
if you lost.

39:41.580 --> 39:43.380
Have you seen the news
this evening?

39:43.382 --> 39:44.547
I think I lost.

39:44.549 --> 39:46.149
I think you lost
on purpose.

39:46.151 --> 39:47.917
Well, why the hell
would I do that?

39:49.154 --> 39:51.087
What else did you have
on Mellie, Abby?

39:51.089 --> 39:52.989
Nothing. I thought
the psychic was enough.

39:52.991 --> 39:55.191
-Abby.
-What?

39:55.193 --> 39:57.193
Mellie going off the deep end
and consulting a crystal ball

39:57.195 --> 39:59.429
doesn't exactly spell future
leader of the free world to me.

39:59.431 --> 40:02.499
What else did you have
on Mellie, Abby?

40:02.501 --> 40:04.701
I saw the folder.

40:04.703 --> 40:06.436
I know
there was something in there.

40:06.438 --> 40:07.670
What did you have
on Mellie?

40:13.712 --> 40:15.211
[ Sighs ]

40:15.213 --> 40:17.447
I didn't have anything
on Mellie.

40:17.449 --> 40:18.882
It wasn't her?

40:18.884 --> 40:20.683
It --

40:23.722 --> 40:25.588
It was me.
You had something on me?

40:27.626 --> 40:29.793
The night Mellie
won her filibuster,

40:29.795 --> 40:32.095
the night you moved
out of the White House...

40:35.033 --> 40:36.199
My abortion.

40:36.201 --> 40:37.600
I didn't want to hurt you.

40:39.738 --> 40:41.805
Thank you.

40:44.075 --> 40:46.109
That would have been
a smart move for a campaign --

40:46.111 --> 40:47.944
taking down Mellie
by shaming me.

40:47.946 --> 40:51.448
But the thing is,
I'm not ashamed at all.

40:51.450 --> 40:55.485
The only person who would have
really been hurt is him.

40:55.487 --> 40:58.588
It would have hurt him.

40:58.590 --> 41:02.091
And not just publicly.

41:02.093 --> 41:03.593
[ Sighs ]

41:03.595 --> 41:04.828
Abby.

41:08.400 --> 41:09.499
He doesn't know.

41:12.604 --> 41:15.171
No one knows.
How did you find out?

41:15.173 --> 41:17.474
Your father told me.

41:18.910 --> 41:22.879
And, Liv, I don't think
he's done with you.

41:25.617 --> 41:27.584
[ Door opens ]

41:32.924 --> 41:34.591
[ Door closes ]
I'm not going to apologize.

41:34.593 --> 41:35.959
I said
what had to be said.

41:35.961 --> 41:37.961
No apologies necessary,
son.

41:37.963 --> 41:40.330
I just need to confirm
what I already know.

41:40.332 --> 41:42.665
That speech
was Olivia's idea.

41:42.667 --> 41:47.470
She saved you and beat me.
Hmm?

41:47.472 --> 41:50.640
You're not crafty enough to
execute that move on your own.

41:50.642 --> 41:51.841
You can't hurt me.

41:51.843 --> 41:53.276
Luckily, I don't have to.

41:53.278 --> 41:55.011
Listen, I am nobody--

41:56.781 --> 41:58.515
Fool.

41:58.517 --> 42:00.049
I'm gonna allow you to live

42:00.051 --> 42:02.185
because Rowan may need you
in the future.

42:02.187 --> 42:03.887
I would have made
a fantastic Vice President.

42:03.889 --> 42:05.288
You really missed out.

42:05.290 --> 42:07.123
We would have had
some fun times.

42:09.628 --> 42:11.294
Tell Liv I need her help.

42:11.296 --> 42:12.795
Tell her I want to escape.

42:12.797 --> 42:15.532
Tell her
I'm chasing the sun.

42:17.969 --> 42:19.602
[ Breathing shakily ]

42:22.541 --> 42:25.875
[<i> Camera shutter clicks</i> ]

42:38.423 --> 42:41.558
♪♪
